fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Let \Bbbk  / \mathbb {F} be a finite Galois extension. The correspondences
\begin {split}\{\hbox {subgroups }H\leq \mathop {\textrm {Gal}}\nolimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F})\} & \to \{\hbox {subfields }\mathbb {L}\subseteq \Bbbk \mid  \mathbb {F}\subseteq \mathbb {L}\}\\ H & \mapsto \Bbbk ^{H}\end {split}
and
\begin {split}\{\hbox {subfields }\mathbb {L}\subseteq \Bbbk \mid  \mathbb {F}\subseteq \mathbb {L}\}&\to \{\hbox {subgroups }H\leq \mathop {\textrm {Gal}}\nolimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F})\}\\ \mathbb {L} & \mapsto \mathop {\textrm {Aut}}\nolimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {L})\subseteq \mathop {\textrm {Gal}}\nolimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F})\end {split}
are bijections satisfying the following properties:

fr:ol.fr:li:
The Galois correspondence

  \usepackage {quiver, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs}
  \begin {tikzcd}
  \mathbf {1}\ar [r]\arrow [d,"|H|",dash,swap] & \Bbbk \arrow [d,"{[\Bbbk  : \Bbbk ^{H}]}",dash]\\
  H\ar [r]\arrow [d,"{[G:H]}",dash,swap] & \Bbbk \ar [d,"{[\mathbb {L} : \mathbb {F}]}",dash] \\
  G\ar [r] & \mathbb {F}
  \end {tikzcd}


preserves the index. In other words
[\Bbbk  : \Bbbk ^{H}]=|H|,
and
[G : H]=[\Bbbk ^{H} : \mathbb {F}].

Let \mathbb {L}_{1}=\Bbbk ^{H_{1}} and \mathbb {L}_{2}=\Bbbk ^{H_{2}}, then
\mathbb {L}_{1}\cap  \mathbb {L}_{2}=\Bbbk ^{\langle  H_{1},H_{2}\rangle }
where \langle  H_{1},H_{2}\rangle  is the subgroup of G generated by the union of the underlying sets, and
\mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2}=\Bbbk ^{H_{1}\cap  H_{2}}
where \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2} is the composite of \mathbb {L}_{1} and \mathbb {L}_{2}.

