We saw earlier that the composition of these
H\mapsto \Bbbk ^{H}\mapsto \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk  / \Bbbk ^{H})
are the identity function. But composing these correspondences in the opposite order
\mathbb {L}\mapsto \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {L})\mapsto \Bbbk ^{\mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {L})}
does not always give us the identity function. But it is true that \mathbb {L}\subseteq \Bbbk ^{\mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {L})} (although \Bbbk ^{\mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {L})} may be strictly larger than \mathbb {L} which happens for \Bbbk =\mathbb {Q}(\sqrt [3]{2}) and \mathbb {F}=\mathbb {Q} where \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F})=1 is trivial so \Bbbk ^{\mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F})}=\Bbbk  properly contains \mathbb {F}).

(3) Since \mathbb {L}_{1}\subseteq \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2} and \mathbb {L}_{2}\subseteq \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2}, we have \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits _{\mathbb {F}}(\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2})\subseteq H_{1}\cap H_{2}. Conversely, if \sigma \in H_{1}\cap H_{2}, it fixes \mathbb {L}_{1} and \mathbb {L}_{2}. Since \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2} is generated by \mathbb {L}_{1} and \mathbb {L}_{2} over \mathbb {F}, \sigma also fixes \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2}. Then H_{1}\cap H_{2}\subseteq \mathop {	extrm {Aut}}
olimits _{\mathbb {F}}(\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2}). Therefore \mathop {	extrm {Gal}}
olimits (\Bbbk / \mathbb {L}_{1}\mathbb {L}_{2})=H_{1}\cap H_{2}, which establishes the first claim of (3).

Let \Bbbk / \mathbb {F} be Galois, let G=\mathop {	extrm {Gal}}
olimits (\Bbbk / \mathbb {F}), and let \mathbb {L}=\Bbbk ^{H} for H\leq G. Then (1) map  egin {split}\mathop {	extrm {Gal}}
