fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Let \Bbbk _{1} / \mathbb {F} and \Bbbk _{2} / \mathbb {F} be subextensions of some extension \mathbb {L} / \mathbb {F}, as in the following diagram:

  \usepackage {quiver, amsopn, amssymb, mathrsfs}
  \begin {tikzcd}
    & \ar [dl, dash] \mathbb {L} \ar [dr, dash] & \\
\Bbbk _{1} \ar [dr, dash] & & \ar [dl, dash] \Bbbk _{2}\\
    &   \mathbb {F}   &
  \end {tikzcd}

The Composite Field of \Bbbk _{1} with \Bbbk _{2} is the smallest field subfield denoted \Bbbk _{1}\Bbbk _{2} of \mathbb {L} containing both \Bbbk _{1} and \Bbbk _{2}.
